N. Rüdinger (1530-1581) eine der bisher zu wenig beachteten Schlüsselfiguren im Netzwerk des pfälzischen Späthumanismus vorgestellt. Zeitkritische Satiren, Facetten der Kasualpoesie, vor allem das weite Feld der elegischen Bibeldichtung gewinnen dabei genaue Konturen in Kontexten der Antike und Frühen Neuzeit.  aThis monograph - which stands out due to its use of archival documents, editions, translations, commentaries, and interpretations - introduces the school principal, Latin poet, and comital treasurer N. Rüdinger, one of the key figures of late Palatine humanism, who has thus far received too little attention. It presents his critical satires, casual poetry, and elegiac bible adaptations in the context of the ancient and early modern periods.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 4aFrühe Neuzeit. 4aHumanismus. 4aLyrik. 4aNeulatein. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aBeichert, Karl Wilhelm, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2021z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831107238160 cprintz978311072363240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311072367040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110723670423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110723670.jpg  a978-3-11-075070-6  DG Ebook Package 2021b2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DKUb2021